What does it do? It tells you it has 'x' number of items to upload. It doesn't upload them, despite the fact that I've set it up according to the meagre instructions. Pointless add-on to an otherwise excellent app.
replyContent: Autotransfer starts the transfer of the 'x' number of items when the autotransfer trigger that you chose 'fires'. Depending on the trigger this could happen when you connect to a certain Wi-Fi network or when you take a new photo or when you scheduled a transfer etc. If you have problems, feel free to contact our support, we are happy to help.

replyContent: Thank you for your helpful review. There is only one reason for that extra icon: The extra app contains the license for the Autotransfer Add-On. I case you don't know, you don't need to link the icon to your phone desktop and you can even hide it in the app list on your device. Sadly icons are part of an operating system.

replyContent: Depends on how you configure the VPN connection. Photosync uses normal network connections so it should work with VPN as well. You might have problems with the automatic device detection if your VPN is not handling Multicast requests. We use it with VPN without any problems.
